response.question: Q4: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n).
response.feedback: Score: 1.0/1.0. Graded against Assignment Description and standard academic correctness. The student correctly identified the time complexity of a linear search. The answer O(n) is the correct Big O notation, as the time to complete the search grows linearly with the number of items (n) in the list.
